            <h2>What is WWW?</h2>
            <p>The World Wide Web (WWW) is a system of interlinked hypertext documents accessed via the Internet. It was invented by Tim Berners-Lee in 1989 and has revolutionized the way we share information and connect with one another.</p>
            <p>Using web browsers, users can access multimedia pages, navigate through links, and interact with content.</p>
